definitions.definition: A rule or principle , especially one governing personal conduct .
A written command , especially a demand for payment .
An order issued by one local authority to another specifying the rate of tax to be charged on its behalf.

subdefinitions.definition: A rate or tax set by a precept.

main_definition: A rule or principle , especially one governing personal conduct .

( UK ) An order issued by one local authority to another specifying the rate of tax to be charged on its behalf.
